de.ityx.tools.trie.simple

Class TrieMatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ityx.tools.trie.simple.TrieMatcher

  • public class TrieMatcher
extends Object
    The class TrieMatcher was designed to perform fast matching operations on a given String.
    A TrieMatcher is created by invoking the matcher-method of class Trie, which is strongly recommended, or directly via the public constructors.

    Once a TrieMatcher was created, it can perfom matching operations by using the find-method. It returns a boolean to indicate if it was successful or not. In case of a succesful match information about the position of the match can be obtained via the start and end-methods.

    So, as you may noticed, it works similar to class Matcher of package java.util.regex .
    Author:
    arenz
